        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 8:08PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 808 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Chamblissburg, or 7 miles east of Stewartsville, moving east at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Bedford...
Moneta...
Thaxton...
Goodview...
Chamblissburg...
and Goode.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM EDT for
central Virginia.</instruction>
